@et304383 IMO you're correct about user expectations, but I think @jamesls is concerned about correctness.  Here's the kind of thing I'd be concerned about.

If botocore uses the same cache as awscli, the cache is now shared global state - that brings the risk of concurrent update bugs.  Keeping botocore's cache somewhere else is simpler than working out a robust, cross-platform locking scheme.  And doesn't awscli + patched botocore trigger this race condition?  awscli uses botocore to get temp creds, and both will race to update the cache.  (AFAICT nothing ensures that the cache update is finished being written when the result is returned to the caller.)

So the new location is safer.  If this is accepted, I imagine the awscli cache should be removed.

