The issue I have here is that the `except KeyError` catches, by my count, 5 possible exceptions (at least, that I can see... excluding any function calls made within this code).

The behavior we're seeing is that LeaderNotAvailable() is thrown on any of these `KeyError`'s, and what's more, since the exception isn't chained, we don't know which one. I'm wondering if `brokers[meta.leader]` is giving a `KeyError` because `meta.leader` == -1 (and thus, no broker exists with that key), and that this explains the overzealousness of the exception. But, this is just a hunch. Could be any number of other conditions.

