@saraneem I promise this is an error in proxy configuration. It also has nothing to do with conda, but is an error in requests/urllib3. @nehaljwani has gotten a fix into upstream requests, but after months they still haven’t had a release with the change. 

The information you’ve provided show that both `HTTP_PROXY` and `HTTPS_PROXY` environment variables are set. Triple check the contents of those environment variables. As I recall, the most common cause of this error is missing a `/` in the proxy url. For example, having `http:/proxy.server` instead of `http://proxy.server`. 

Also, requests picks proxy configuration out of the windows registry. We don’t report that in `confa info` right now, but we should.

